{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "878e907f-a042-4495-a817-7ee6774617a2",
		"name": "Community Mgmt API betagrid",
		"description": "## TGCommunity Services REST API's\n\n[https://developer.opentext.com/ce/products/active-community/apis/community-management-services-trading-grid](https://developer.opentext.com/ce/products/active-community/apis/community-management-services-trading-grid)\n\nFor the calls below you need the BUID / companyId **GC51278300AS**\n\n- You can get a list of users for a company, which includes userId, loginId, email, lastName, firstName\n    \n\nOne thing that is a bit confusing is that\n\n- to find a particular user’s userId, you need to search loginId validuserid@somewhere.com\n    \n- to retrieve a user’s details you use either loginId validuserid@somewhere.com or userId **GCPHO01O61184**\n    \n- to retrieve a user’s roles, you need to use loginId validuserid@somewhere.com\n    \n\nThe APIs do not allow searches by email address or by name.\n\nSo, as a normal client of the API, I would know my BUID. To get a list of roles for “Firstname Lastname”\n\n1. retrieve list all users of my BUID\n    \n2. search that json for firstName = Firstname and lastName = Lastname\n    \n3. use the loginId of that user object to return the list of roles\n    \n\n**loginId** may be changed by the user within TGO. Therefore, every effort to look at or update users or roles would **require retreiving the list of all users first**",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
		"_exporter_id": "5147552"
	},
